    <div class="article">
      <p>You must tell the Traffic Commissioner about offences that involve:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>anybody you’ve named in your application</li>
        <li>companies directed by anybody you’ve named</li>
        <li>parent companies, if you’re a limited company</li>
      </ul>
      <details class="help">
        <summary class="help__summary">Which offences do they need to know about?</summary>
        <div class="help__text">
          <p>The Traffic Commissioner needs to know if anybody you’ve named has been convicted of an offence related to:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>the Goods Vehicles (Licensing of Operators) Act 1995</li>
            <li>the Transport Act 1968 or the Road Traffic Act 1960</li>
            <li>section 13 of the Hydrocarbon Oil Duties Act 1979</li>
            <li>sections 53, 74, 173 and 174 of the Road Traffic Act 1988 </li>
            <li>keeping goods vehicles in a fit an serviceable condition</li>
            <li>section 2 of the International Road Haulage Permits Act 1975</li>
            <li>section 3 of the Control of Pollution Act 1974</li>
            <li>section 2 of the Refuse Disposal (Amenity) Act 1978</li>
            <li>section 1 of the Control of Pollution (Amendment) Act 1989</li>
            <li>section 33 of the Environmental Protection Act 1990</li>
            <li>speed limits, driver licensing and driver hours </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </details>
