    <div class="article">
      <h3>Standard National and Standard International licences</h3>
      <p>If you’re applying for a standard national or international licence, the Traffic Commissioner also needs to know about similar convictions under the laws of Northern Ireland or any country outside the UK.</p>
      <p>You must let them know them about any convictions where the punishment was either:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>imprisonment for longer than three months</li>
        <li>a fine above level 4 on the standard scale</li>
        <li>a community service order (or the equivalent) involving unpaid work for more than 60 hours</li>
        <li>any conviction or penalty for an offence under UK law relating to road transport, or any corresponding offence outside the UK </li>
      </ul>
